Villagers of Dikidikini in the Eastern Cape are crossing a river in a locked drum. Risking their lives in the process. They say they have been forced to resort to this extreme measure because government has forgotten them. Nceba Ntlanganiso reports. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 DIKIDIKINI - Desperate for services, villagers of Dikidikini in the Eastern Cape are crossing a river in a locked drum. They do so risking their lives in the process. They say they have been forced to resort to this extreme measure because government has forgotten them. READ:Â Service delivery protest | Komga residents have had enough Those who are brave enough, swim across the river. eNCA contacted the Eastern Cape Road and Transport Department and have, at the time of publication not replied. Watch the video above for more details on this story.